The paper deals with the problem of sparse signal recovery from noisy linear measurements using composite regularization. This is a problem that is studied in several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistical inference (cs.SI). Given that the paper proposes new algorithms for this problem and provides several interpretations of them, it is likely to be relevant to all of these sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on the specific problem of sparse signal recovery, we expect cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.SP to be the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.NA and cs.SI.
